result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason J Wendels was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 11/18/2016 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.

Consecutive to: Court sentenced defendant to serve 10 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for 34 days served; Huber privileges.  Release to the Day Reporting Center.  Court recommends against electronic monitoring.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 
Court does not suspend driving privileges.
